main event: On May 4, 1958, an unidentified cylindrical object was observed in Cerro Catalan, Uruguay, remaining stationary for 6 minutes and emitting a slow pulsing noise.
interesting points: The object was described as cylindrical with no wings,The object emitted a low humming sound while moving,The sighting was compared to a historical event (Chiles Whitted case),Testimony from multiple witnesses indicated a similar description of the object,The object appeared very bright and was said to have a rapid vertical operation.
witness description: witnesses described the object as bright and cylindrical, with a humming sound
